WEBVTT

00:04.212 --> 00:05.588
I miss you.

00:06.756 --> 00:07.924
Natalya’s really gorgeous.

00:07.966 --> 00:09.259
Aussies are my kryptonite.

00:11.636 --> 00:13.722
I don’t know if it’s just
this boat romance

00:13.763 --> 00:16.558
or if it’s blossoming
into something else.

00:18.893 --> 00:20.186
Three meters, getting closer.

00:20.228 --> 00:21.688
Oh sh--,
that’s not three meters.

00:21.730 --> 00:22.731
She’s gonna hit it, man.

00:22.772 --> 00:25.900
We’re gonna hit.

00:25.942 --> 00:27.527
Jesus Christ.

00:27.569 --> 00:29.988
I need to be able to have
a bosun to lead a team,

00:30.030 --> 00:31.573
so I’m letting you go.

00:37.203 --> 00:40.206
I get on with Tash
like a house on fire.

00:40.248 --> 00:43.251
My asshole burns.
My asshole’s like...

00:49.674 --> 00:52.260
Storm is stepping in as a
provisional bosun.

00:52.302 --> 00:53.887
He’s gonna show me
what he’s got.

00:53.928 --> 00:55.722
It’s been a dream of mine
to obviously become a bosun.

00:55.764 --> 00:57.766
And then our
new deckhand arrives

00:57.807 --> 00:58.933
the first day of charter.

00:58.975 --> 01:00.560
-How you doing?
-Nice to see you.

01:00.602 --> 01:04.230
On our last boat, me and Tash,
we got together.

01:07.275 --> 01:08.568
She was still
with her boyfriend,

01:08.610 --> 01:11.404
but she wanted to be with me.

01:11.446 --> 01:13.573
Mm-hmm.

01:13.615 --> 01:16.785
My exes cheated on me, but
it’s not right to cheat back.

01:19.913 --> 01:21.456
I feel betrayed.

01:21.498 --> 01:23.458
Now it’s making me look
like a ----ing idiot.

01:29.464 --> 01:32.175
If you do it again,
you’re fired.

01:32.217 --> 01:34.219
I want you guys
to move cabins now.

01:34.260 --> 01:36.221
I feel like I’ve betrayed you.

01:36.262 --> 01:38.098
I’m obviously very hurt.

01:38.139 --> 01:39.766
I don’t know this person,

01:39.808 --> 01:43.770
I don’t recognize him, and
we work together constantly.

01:43.812 --> 01:46.189
Hopefully he’ll never
do this ever again.

02:15.969 --> 02:18.805
I think there might be a cabin
swap happening today.

02:22.017 --> 02:23.685
It’s happening now.

02:27.480 --> 02:28.815
She’s not going to?

02:34.738 --> 02:36.364
So, you...
that’s what I was gonna say.

02:36.406 --> 02:37.365
So, you guys are gonna swap?

02:37.407 --> 02:38.366
-Yeah.
-Okay, cool.

02:38.408 --> 02:39.784
I don’t have a choice.

02:39.826 --> 02:41.286
Like, they can’t be
sleeping together...

02:41.327 --> 02:42.287
like, in the same room.

02:42.328 --> 02:44.205
-No.
-Shoot, man.

02:44.247 --> 02:45.206
Anyways, let’s bust this out.

02:45.248 --> 02:46.416
All right, buddy.

02:46.458 --> 02:49.210
I did get
most of me out.

02:49.252 --> 02:50.712
I think these are all yours.

02:50.754 --> 02:53.381
I don’t ever wear these,
can I put them somewhere?

02:53.423 --> 02:57.552
I’ll find out if someone
needs some shoes.

02:57.594 --> 03:01.431
Having to move cabins, it’s
kind of like a walk of shame.

03:01.473 --> 03:04.726
The whole time of me trying
to hide this secret

03:04.768 --> 03:08.355
was because I didn’t want
it to disrupt the crew,

03:08.396 --> 03:10.398
I didn’t want it to
cause any drama,

03:10.440 --> 03:12.776
and essentially,
it’s just made things worse.

03:12.817 --> 03:15.570
I’m gonna take half of my
sh-- out of my room now.

03:18.823 --> 03:21.534
I feel like it’s all over now,

03:21.576 --> 03:23.620
and I feel bad
for what I’ve done,

03:23.661 --> 03:26.206
but I’m super disappointed
in myself.

03:26.247 --> 03:29.417
It’s a sh-- feeling.

03:29.459 --> 03:30.543
So, how are you?

03:30.585 --> 03:32.712
I just have to move on.

03:32.754 --> 03:36.466
I don’t know, prove to myself

03:36.508 --> 03:39.386
and to everyone else
that I can do this,

03:39.427 --> 03:40.637
regardless of what’s happened.

03:40.679 --> 03:42.639
Most importantly to yourself.

03:42.681 --> 03:45.058
Through your darkest times
and your happiest moments,

03:45.100 --> 03:47.060
I’m honestly here for you.

03:47.102 --> 03:48.228
Aw.

03:48.269 --> 03:49.854
I’m dead-ass serious about that.

03:53.191 --> 03:56.027
I don’t even know where to
begin with sh-- like this.

03:59.447 --> 04:01.241
<i>Storm, David, Natasha,</i>

04:01.282 --> 04:03.827
let’s meet in the crew mess for
a preference sheet meeting.

04:03.868 --> 04:04.994
On my way.

04:06.079 --> 04:07.539
-Dave?
-Are you okay?

04:11.292 --> 04:12.836
No.

04:14.045 --> 04:15.463
No.

04:20.260 --> 04:22.095
Right, charter number three.

04:22.137 --> 04:25.265
-Yay!
-Yes.

04:25.306 --> 04:27.142
Kristina Rosette is
a real estate agent

04:27.183 --> 04:28.977
in the Bay Area looking
to celebrate

04:29.019 --> 04:31.146
a joint fiftieth birthday party
with her cousin, Dina.

04:31.187 --> 04:35.233
Kristina and Dina are requesting
a dual birthday celebration

04:35.275 --> 04:36.776
and prefer their cake

04:36.818 --> 04:39.404
to be delivered by
a shirtless deckhand.

04:39.446 --> 04:40.822
Hundred percent Mzi.

04:40.864 --> 04:41.990
[sneezes]

04:42.032 --> 04:43.616
For the final night of charter,

04:43.658 --> 04:46.953
the group would like
to have a Studio 54 party

04:46.995 --> 04:48.038
with glitter décor.

04:48.079 --> 04:49.497
Yes!
So excited for that.

04:49.539 --> 04:52.167
These ladies have a
high threshold for adventure

04:52.208 --> 04:53.710
and are aiming to spend
as much time

04:53.752 --> 04:56.087
with the water toys as possible.

04:56.129 --> 04:57.797
We’re gonna flood the back.

04:57.839 --> 04:58.965
Thank you.

04:59.007 --> 05:00.383
It’s gonna be an
adventure land for them.

05:00.425 --> 05:02.344
I’ve never been a bosun before,

05:02.385 --> 05:05.138
but Sandy feels
that she can entrust

05:05.180 --> 05:07.182
this provisional title on me.

05:07.223 --> 05:10.310
It’s exciting,
and it’s nerve-wracking.

05:10.352 --> 05:13.104
I will give 250 percent
from the moment

05:13.146 --> 05:14.731
I wake up till the moment
I go to sleep.

05:14.773 --> 05:16.066
What kind of cake you thinking?

05:16.107 --> 05:18.026
I’ll do, like,
a three-tier one,

05:18.068 --> 05:19.819
do a massive one,
like a wedding cake.

05:19.861 --> 05:21.571
Like a vanilla?

05:21.613 --> 05:23.865
I’ll do, like, classic
vanilla sponge.

05:23.907 --> 05:25.867
Yeah, they both
like vanilla cake.

05:25.909 --> 05:27.660
In the past I’ve had couples.

05:27.702 --> 05:31.373
I’ve had two that
turned out in a very good way,

05:31.414 --> 05:34.668
and the other 20 were not.

05:34.709 --> 05:37.045
David and Natasha
are demonstrating

05:37.087 --> 05:38.380
their professionalism right now.

05:38.421 --> 05:39.923
They’re both excellent
at their craft,

05:39.964 --> 05:41.758
and they’ve been doing
this a long time.

05:41.800 --> 05:43.593
I think they can do this.

05:43.635 --> 05:45.387
So, let’s have an awesome
charter tomorrow.

05:45.428 --> 05:47.847
-Yep.
-Get a good night’s sleep

05:47.889 --> 05:50.600
I’ve only got, like, 30 more
shirts to iron, thank God.

06:02.529 --> 06:03.863
I think that’s it.

06:03.905 --> 06:05.115
All right, well,
that’s everyone’s laundry

06:05.156 --> 06:06.700
done for the next year.

06:06.741 --> 06:07.659
Ah!

06:08.868 --> 06:10.829
Did you just say,
"Kyle is a Hawaiian?"

06:17.419 --> 06:18.712
Is that your favorite?

06:18.753 --> 06:20.255
-Ah!
-Are you ticklish?

06:20.296 --> 06:23.508
How can you have foot
massages if you’re ticklish?

06:23.550 --> 06:25.719
I’ve never had good experiences
with boyfriends.

06:25.760 --> 06:28.722
So, I have got trust issues,

06:28.763 --> 06:31.141
but with Storm, we’re
a little bit romantic.

06:31.182 --> 06:33.601
I don’t know what’s happening,
I don’t know what’s happening.

06:37.439 --> 06:40.275
-A what?
-I’ve got a big day.

06:40.316 --> 06:41.401
No, I said...

06:41.443 --> 06:42.902
[laughing]

06:42.944 --> 06:44.863
Do you wanna hear the
waterfalls, babe?

06:44.904 --> 06:46.781
What waterfalls?

06:48.616 --> 06:50.076
It’s Niagara Falls, hon.

06:50.118 --> 06:51.453
Oh, so...

06:53.371 --> 06:55.373
Oh sh--, was that your...
did I put it in your cupboard?

06:55.415 --> 06:56.833
-Dude, you’re good, bro.
-Sorry.

06:56.875 --> 06:58.877
Dave’s been having
a really tough day.

06:58.918 --> 07:00.045
I feel for him.

07:00.086 --> 07:01.588
Granted, I probably
would feel different

07:01.629 --> 07:03.214
if I know the whole story.

07:03.256 --> 07:06.217
Even though we might have
been off to a rocky start...

07:06.259 --> 07:08.303
No, don’t touch me.

07:08.345 --> 07:09.971
Me and Dave are cool.

07:10.013 --> 07:12.349
But now that we’re roommates,
like, mind your business,

07:12.390 --> 07:17.979
stay clean, don’t use Axe
deodorizers in the ----ing room.

07:19.606 --> 07:23.109
Turns out I have a little OCD.

07:23.151 --> 07:25.153
Sleep well, mate.

07:34.329 --> 07:36.915
Charter three.

07:38.667 --> 07:40.126
Natalya, Natalya, Tasha.

07:40.168 --> 07:42.754
Can you meet me
in the stew pantry?

07:42.796 --> 07:44.506
-Copy that.
-Morning, guvna.

07:44.547 --> 07:45.924
Morning, mate.

07:45.965 --> 07:47.550
So, today...

07:47.592 --> 07:48.968
so, I need to sort the flowers,

07:49.010 --> 07:50.804
we’ll need to clean
the main deck day head.

07:50.845 --> 07:52.347
Okay, I’ll do that first.

07:52.389 --> 07:54.474
They’re gonna have champagne
as their welcome drink,

07:54.516 --> 07:57.435
and then sit for lunch.

07:57.477 --> 07:58.978
Can I do, like,
a nautical theme?

07:59.020 --> 08:00.563
We’ll grab those hats out,
just to start off?

08:00.605 --> 08:02.107
Yes, get the sailor hats on.

08:02.148 --> 08:03.733
All right, I’m gonna
start the day head.

08:03.775 --> 08:04.818
Sailor’s hat.

08:04.859 --> 08:06.152
Where’d you want me to get now?

08:06.194 --> 08:07.779
Do you wanna just start
banging out that laz?

08:07.821 --> 08:09.155
I’m just gonna hit
the scuppers quickly.

08:09.197 --> 08:10.615
Cool.

08:18.373 --> 08:19.624
He is not single.

08:29.676 --> 08:32.345
-Hello?
-Hello! Hey.

08:32.387 --> 08:33.680
Coming up...

08:33.722 --> 08:35.515
Six meters [garbled
radio chatter] stern.

08:35.557 --> 08:36.808
I don’t hear Storm.

08:36.850 --> 08:38.268
Three meters to
V4 off your...

08:38.309 --> 08:39.352
[garbled transmission]

08:54.993 --> 08:55.410
-Hello?
-Hi!

08:56.578 --> 08:58.913
-Hi!
-So good to see you.

08:58.955 --> 09:00.582
You, too, how are you?

09:00.623 --> 09:03.960
Good, it’s been great to
know what you’ve been up to.

09:04.002 --> 09:05.587
Oh, yeah, so much.

09:05.628 --> 09:07.589
-How’ve you been?
-Good.

09:07.630 --> 09:09.466
Oh, I’m excited to
be back, but...

09:09.507 --> 09:10.550
-Yeah.
-I’m a bit...

09:10.592 --> 09:11.551
I’m very nervous to be on deck.

09:11.593 --> 09:13.178
I’m back!

09:13.219 --> 09:15.805
I was kind of in two
minds after last season.

09:15.847 --> 09:17.390
Like, being promoted
to second stew.

09:17.432 --> 09:19.309
I do wanna give you these.

09:19.351 --> 09:20.769
Stop!

09:20.810 --> 09:22.228
I feel like I used to
go on boats and be, like,

09:22.270 --> 09:24.314
known as the wild one,
the crazy one.

09:24.356 --> 09:26.441
* We’re here in the galley
and we’re chillin’ with daddy *

09:26.483 --> 09:29.110
* We’ve got a lot going on but
we’re feeling so swaggy *

09:29.152 --> 09:32.155
Last season it was so intense,

09:32.197 --> 09:36.159
and I was constantly inside and
stressed and never saw daylight.

09:42.707 --> 09:43.958
I definitely feel like
a deckhand, like,

09:44.000 --> 09:45.669
fits my personally
better than a stew.

09:45.710 --> 09:46.795
Courtney’s switching
to deck crew.

09:46.836 --> 09:48.421
This is epic!

09:48.463 --> 09:50.507
Getting the call from
Sandy to come back,

09:50.548 --> 09:53.510
I’m excited, but I’m,
like, super nervous as well.

09:53.551 --> 09:55.303
I’m ready to get to twerk.

09:57.222 --> 09:59.724
Oh, there’s Mzi!

09:59.766 --> 10:01.601
-Hi!
-Hey!

10:01.643 --> 10:04.062
-How are you?
-How are you?

10:04.104 --> 10:05.271
Yeah, not so bad, thank you.

10:05.313 --> 10:06.398
Good!

10:06.439 --> 10:08.817
I love Mzi’s face
when he sees you.

10:08.858 --> 10:09.984
Can you show me everyone?

10:10.026 --> 10:11.820
-Yeah.
-I’m Courtney, hi.

10:11.861 --> 10:12.862
Jason, nice to meet you.

10:12.904 --> 10:14.322
Hi, nice to meet you.

10:14.364 --> 10:15.699
Storm, would you like to meet
the new deckhand?

10:15.740 --> 10:16.908
Hi!

10:16.950 --> 10:17.992
Hi, have you got
your bags on board?

10:18.034 --> 10:19.494
I’m gonna grab it in a second,

10:19.536 --> 10:20.662
but I just wanted
to come on and meet everyone.

10:20.704 --> 10:21.663
Yeah, sure.

10:21.705 --> 10:22.831
Is Storm your real name?

10:22.872 --> 10:24.040
-It is indeed.
-That’s so cool!

10:24.082 --> 10:25.917
-Lovely to meet you.
-Yeah, you too.

10:28.878 --> 10:30.714
I’m so, so stoked to
have Courtney back.

10:30.755 --> 10:32.757
Courtney’s definitely gonna
bring a twerk to the team,

10:32.799 --> 10:35.343
and some good banter, too.

10:35.385 --> 10:38.888
After Lady Michelle,
she did come to Cape Town.

10:38.930 --> 10:40.974
We’ve both come such a
long way in terms of

10:41.016 --> 10:45.145
our actual friendship and
I’ve grown even fonder of Court.

10:45.186 --> 10:47.147
[laughing]

10:50.233 --> 10:52.235
I...

10:52.277 --> 10:54.195
No.

10:54.237 --> 10:57.699
I... [laughing]

10:57.741 --> 10:59.034
No.

10:59.075 --> 11:00.702
Hi, I’m Courtney,
nice to meet you.

11:00.744 --> 11:01.828
-Nice to meet you!
-What’s your name?

11:01.870 --> 11:02.829
-Tasha.
-Tasha...

11:02.871 --> 11:03.913
nice to meet you, Tasha.

11:03.955 --> 11:05.331
How are you?
Oh, sorry.

11:05.373 --> 11:06.833
-Dave, nice to meet you.
-Courtney, nice to meet you.

11:06.875 --> 11:08.376
-Welcome aboard.
-Thank you.

11:08.418 --> 11:09.836
I’ve just put your uniform
on your bed, Courtney.

11:09.878 --> 11:11.421
Oh, thank you so much.

11:18.178 --> 11:19.387
Do you want a tea or coffee?

11:19.429 --> 11:20.555
Yeah, all right.

11:20.597 --> 11:21.806
-Hi!
-I’m Natalya.

11:21.848 --> 11:23.558
Hi, Courtney, nice to meet you.

11:23.600 --> 11:24.809
I’m your roomie.

11:26.353 --> 11:28.605
There’s Natasha
and then Natalya.

11:28.646 --> 11:29.981
-Okay.
-So, we’re called...

11:30.023 --> 11:31.232
-Natasha and Natalya.
-Yeah, Tash and Nat.

11:31.274 --> 11:32.525
Okay, and while
you’re on board...

11:32.567 --> 11:33.735
-I’m Nat.
-No, I know.

11:33.777 --> 11:35.987
Oh, wow...
wow, I’m screaming.

11:36.029 --> 11:37.113
-We’re both second stews.
-Second, yeah.

11:37.155 --> 11:38.531
-Okay, nice.
-Yeah.

11:38.573 --> 11:40.575
Deck crew, deck crew,
please can you meet me

11:40.617 --> 11:41.743
on the aft deck
for a quick meeting?

11:41.785 --> 11:42.952
Copy.

11:44.621 --> 11:45.872
-Hello.
-Hello.

11:45.914 --> 11:48.958
-So, welcome to the crew.
-Thank you.

11:49.000 --> 11:53.296
For this charter, I did
print a new deck schedule.

11:53.338 --> 11:55.507
You will have everything there,
it’s your hours of watch.

11:55.548 --> 11:59.094
In the evening, we do really try
to help out the interior.

11:59.135 --> 12:00.053
Yeah.

12:00.095 --> 12:01.012
Well, you know what that’s like.

12:01.054 --> 12:02.597
For this whole charter, like,

12:02.639 --> 12:04.557
if you see thing that are
lying around, pick them up.

12:04.599 --> 12:06.142
Just the small things that’ll
make the biggest difference.

12:06.184 --> 12:08.103
And then I’m sure
we’ll have a great time.

12:08.144 --> 12:09.604
I’m a very intense person.

12:09.646 --> 12:11.231
I have an enlarged heart.

12:11.272 --> 12:14.234
I was in Sri Lanka in 2019.
I was just surfing.

12:14.275 --> 12:17.946
I just felt this, like,
crazy drop in my heart,

12:17.987 --> 12:19.531
like, I couldn’t
breathe properly,

12:19.572 --> 12:21.241
my arm started to go numb.

12:23.993 --> 12:25.995
I had to have surgery,
which is cardioversion.

12:26.037 --> 12:27.789
So, they stop your heart
and then they restart it.

12:27.831 --> 12:29.165
I was dead for two minutes.

12:29.207 --> 12:31.292
It definitely changed my mindset

12:31.334 --> 12:33.211
to just live
as hardcore as I can.

12:33.253 --> 12:35.422
Everything that I’m gonna
do now, I’m gonna overdo.

12:35.463 --> 12:38.591
Grab a microfiber, where the
scuppers are clean the drains,

12:38.633 --> 12:39.968
just so they walk on
and it’s beautiful.

12:40.010 --> 12:41.177
-Yeah.
-Thanks, guys.

12:41.219 --> 12:42.345
Sure.

12:42.387 --> 12:43.722
I can’t wait.

12:43.763 --> 12:45.098
This is gonna be such a fun
little table setting.

12:45.140 --> 12:46.307
I’ve got your hat.

12:46.349 --> 12:48.309
I wish this was
actually our uniform.

12:48.351 --> 12:50.478
Hit me,
I’ll do this side underneath.

12:50.520 --> 12:51.688
Yeah, it’s gross.

12:51.730 --> 12:53.314
I’m actually really
nervous for, like...

12:53.356 --> 12:56.735
I just need to know how to
do the anchor and sh--.

12:56.776 --> 12:58.445
No, it’s all Gucci.

12:58.486 --> 13:00.488
Provisions, eh?

13:00.530 --> 13:01.865
All crew, all crew,
we have provisions.

13:05.493 --> 13:07.495
All right.

13:07.537 --> 13:09.122
Ooh!

13:10.206 --> 13:11.624
-You all right there?
-Yeah, yeah.

13:11.666 --> 13:12.625
Yeah?

13:12.667 --> 13:14.044
The Leaning Tower of Pisa.

13:15.670 --> 13:17.839
How is this all
gonna fit, Mzi?

13:17.881 --> 13:19.716
It’s a bit of a mystery.

13:19.758 --> 13:21.092
Tonight is, like,
the big night

13:21.134 --> 13:22.886
for the fiftieth birthday for
the primary.

13:25.347 --> 13:26.598
Yas.

13:26.639 --> 13:29.434
<i>Interior, interior,</i>
<i>looking fab, well done.</i>

13:29.476 --> 13:31.561
I wish I could say
the same for Kyle.

13:31.603 --> 13:32.937
This one drives me insane.

13:35.899 --> 13:38.568
[bleep]
These swells are not good.

13:38.610 --> 13:41.154
We have a charter
boarding today, and right now,

13:41.196 --> 13:42.697
the dock,
the wind’s kinda calm.

13:42.739 --> 13:44.991
For the lay person,
they have no idea the minute

13:45.033 --> 13:47.160
I turn that corner
how big the swells are.

13:47.202 --> 13:48.328
They’re massive.

